<figureCitation id="6AB2EBDDEC3FFFCFFEE76C2BFE56CC5D" box="[347,498,1607,1631]" captionStart-0="FIG" captionStart-1="FIG" captionStart-2="FIG" captionStartId-0="19.[161,177,861,883]" captionStartId-1="19.[245,261,1550,1572]" captionStartId-2="20.[160,176,494,516]" captionTargetBox-0="[456,810,171,824]" captionTargetBox-1="[362,904,959,1511]" captionTargetBox-2="[372,902,171,457]" captionTargetId-0="figure-43@19.[453,811,170,827]" captionTargetId-1="figure-64@19.[359,906,955,1517]" captionTargetId-2="figure-82@20.[371,904,170,460]" captionTargetPageId-0="19" captionTargetPageId-1="19" captionTargetPageId-2="20" captionText-0="FIG. 17. Limatula smithi. Sta. 191, lateral view of shell from right side. Scale bar: 1 mm." captionText-1="FIG. 18. Limatula smithi. Sta. 189, dorsal view of shell. Scale bar: 1 mm." captionText-2="FIG. 19. Limatula smithi. Sta. Valorous 11, internal view of hinge of left valve. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5250755" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5250757" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5250761" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5250755/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5250757/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5250761/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="2608">figures 17–19</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="6AB2EBDDEC3FFFCFFDB56C2BFD95CC5D" box="[521,561,1607,1631]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="41.[154,170,1438,1460]" captionTargetBox="[156,1109,170,1402]" captionTargetId="figure-73@41.[156,1109,170,1405]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIG. 45. SEM photographs of species of Limatula. (a) L. louiseae; (b) L. margaretae; (c) L. smithi; (d) L. celtica.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5250842" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5250842/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="2608">45c</figureCitation>
). Shell moderately small (maximum recorded height 11.7 mm), height/length ratio 1:0.59, moderately fragile, inflated, length/width ratio 1:0.90, equivalve, very slightly ineqilateral with posterior margin slightly more narrowly curved than anterior, transluscent white, ornamented by straight radial ribs crossed by variously spaced concentric incremental lines, radial ribs number 40–48, except antero- and postero-dorsally close to ears ribs extend over entire shell, lateral ribs progressively less well-defined, small sharply pointed reticulations occur where ribs and concentric lines cross, two central ribs larger than remainder, internally shell centrally deeply channelled, ears relatively small, subauricular sinuses present, anterior the more pronounced; umbos prominent, beak pointed, dorsal hinge margin very slightly concave on either side of mid-point; hinge plate with central grooves on either side of resilium into which fit extended ligament, resilium and central ligament broadly oval. Prodissoconch I length~ 
<emphasis id="C0FD2B4AEC39FFC9FE4C6915FDADC993" box="[496,521,889,913]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="2610">ca</emphasis>
110 
<emphasis id="C0FD2B4AEC39FFC9FD876915FDEEC993" box="[571,586,889,913]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="2610">M</emphasis>
m; interdissoconch indistinct, 
<emphasis id="C0FD2B4AEC39FFC9FC2A6915FC0BC993" box="[918,943,889,913]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="2610">ca</emphasis>
0.7 mm.
</paragraph>
